docs.lead_paragraph: The trend of credits in practically all Latin-American markets during the first quarter of this year was sharply upward, creating a promising situation for exporters planning to expand trade with South America, William Swingle, manager of the foreign department and foreign credit interchange bureau of tire National Association of Credit Men, said yesterday.

docs.lead_paragraph: Six delegates to the Pan-American Commercial Conference, which begins in Buenos Aires on May 26 to continue work started in 1933 under Secretary Hull, sailed yesterday on the Munson liner American Legion. In December, 1933, at Montevideo the American delegation under Mr. Hull laid groundwork for extensive improvements of commercial relations between the United States and Latin-American countries.

docs.snippet: Interest in the foreign exchange market last week centred in the sharp rise in the silver currencies following the Presidential decree lifting the purchase price of domestic silver to 77.57 cents, from 71.11 previously. Silver as a commodity rose in...
docs.lead_paragraph: Interest in the foreign exchange market last week centred in the sharp rise in the silver currencies following the Presidential decree lifting the purchase price of domestic silver to 77.57 cents, from 71.11 previously. Silver as a commodity rose in New York to 81 cents, highest since November, 1920, and in London it touched 36 1/4d, highest since July, 1922.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Chase National Bank, corporate trustee, and M. Ernest Greenebaum Jr., individual trustee, are notifying holders of the Fulnau Corporation first mortgage building and leasehold 6 per cent serial bonds that all the bonds will be redeemed on May 15, including interest on overdue interest and a premium of 3 per cent on the principal amount.
